<p class="largefont">View Full Version : World of Warcraft <a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?47891-Frost-Nova-nerf&amp;s=4cfd78a6be599223b3807648a7462719">Frost Nova nerf</a></p>
<hr />
<div class="floatcontainer">  </div><br />
<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 01:22 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Frost Nova has been changed on Player Test Realm so that it breaks as soon as it takes more than a certain amount of damage from a single spell.  So far it seems that a non crit will leave the spell up, and if you're naked, a critical spell still has the same chance not to break, however when geared, a critical spell will break Frost Nova, Freeze, and Frost Bite every single time.  We need more testing to figure out the new &quot;break&quot; formula,  but regardless, this is a huge fucking nerf.<br />
<br />
<br />
Needless to say, I'm pretty unhappy with this, as it makes the Frost tree the weakest PvP tree, and seriously lowers frost DPS on trash mobs.  It also makes Ice Lance a useless toy, since now you'll never get it off on a Frost Bite (by the time the proc shows up, you're usually already halfway done casting another Ice Bolt).<br />
<br />
<br />
Please note: Its on PTR, none of the CM's are talking about it, and its not in the patch messages.  It *could* be a bug, but it really seems like a nerf to something that is only overpowered when you get a huge burst of luck.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Dru</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 01:31 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">If this change goes in, your +damage should increase the breaking point.  Does Frost Nova currently have a chance to break on any damage like Entangling Roots/Fear (pretty sure yes)?  Is this removed with the new change?</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 01:39 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Nope, it can still break like normal, but now instead of having a 40% chance to break on damage (guessing) it has a 90-100% chance to break on Frost Bolt, or something like a 60-70% chance on Ice Lance for a frost mage with Shatter.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Pyre</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 01:40 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Good timing, this may very well save me a respec to arcane/frost to finish leveling. I can just stay arc/fire til 70, and have my hunter farm the billion motes I need for spellcloth.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Mileron</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 01:41 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Nope, it can still break like normal, but now instead of having a 40% chance to break on damage (guessing) it has a 90-100% chance to break on Frost Bolt, or something like a 60-70% chance on Ice Lance for a frost mage with Shatter.<br />
Instead of nerfing Frost Nova, they should reduce Shatter.<br />
<br />
I can't think of any other ability that increases a critical hit by a full 50%.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 03:08 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Updated on the PTR this afternoon: Frost Nova nerf reverted.  Ice Lance now removes Frost Bite and Frost Nova.<br />
<br />
So you're better off casting Frost Bolt again instead of Ice Lance.<br />
<br />
Glad I can stop paying attention when I'm DPSing trash down!  /end sarcasm</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Delaregar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 03:45 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Wow that sucks. The past two mages I've played have been fire, so I was lvling one up on my new server as frost to try it out. Guess it's going to go fire for a third time!</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Maledict</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 05:30 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Nadiar - if you cast icelance as soon as you cast frostbolt on a frozen target, both will hit at the same time and count as hitting a frozen target for the purposes of damage &amp; shatter. Given that, when ice speced, this usually meant 5K damage on a taget in 2.5 seconds, I don't think it's that bad. Certainly when soloing &amp; grinding, the frozen effect ALWAYS broke after doing that. Doesn't matter our distance to the target or anything like that, it works every time as it's a timing issue. So this wont affect solo play at all or group play.<br />
<br />
It is however, a substantial nerf to frost in pvp - but from what I have seen, that might have been needed.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 05:43 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Arc/Frost is still superior in PvP, and it doesn't involve &quot;zomg spam Ice Lance!&quot;<br />
