<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">FilanFyretracker</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 07:09 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">this will harm the more important PvE aspect far more then its going to help shut up useless pvp whiners.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 2nd, 2007, 10:35 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Its back to all crits = break<br />
<br />
http://blue.cardplace.com/newcache/us/80368625.htm<br />
<br />
<br />
The change affects Frost Nova. Frozen targets were never intended to be frozen after a critical. However, the usage of Ice Lance made it very noticable that being frozen was persisting through being crit, whereas normal damage had a chance to break the state. By insuring that a crit will break the frozen state, back to back crits from Ice Lance won't be occurring and such spikes in damage disappear.<br />
<br />
I don't see how it makes Shatter useless, as you are still gaining higher chance of a crit, you just can't two-shot somebody with a zero second cooldown attack.<br />
<br />
This makes shatter completely fucking useless.  Its like a weak version of combustion.</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">reality</div><div class="date">March 3rd, 2007, 01:52 AM</div></div><div class="posttext">saw something like that coming, lots of ice lance whining on the official wow boards ;)<br />
<br />
getting your ice lance launched while the frostbolt is in the air for shatter bonus on both spells is still possible, right? if so it's not that much of a difference, my arc/ice 2800 frostbolt crits already had a ~95% chance to break frozen effects (2200 ice lances like ~90% to break frozen effects)</div></div><hr />


<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Nadiar</div><div class="date">March 3rd, 2007, 03:41 AM</div></div><div class="posttext">No, its a huge difference.  I don't know about you, but I'm already almost done casting the next Frost Bolt by the time the Frostbite proc will even show up.  The people suggesting you always Alternate between FB and Ice Lance aren't calculating in.<br />
<br />
If your Frost Bolts were breaking Frost Nova that often, you either don't pay attention, or you're wrong.  Frostbite, sure.  Frostbite almost never lasted through more than a single crit, and no one really cared.<br />
